One of the Nautilus developer was working to test new changes on a container. He wants to keep a backup of his changes to the container. A new request has been raised for the DevOps team 
to create a new image from this container. Below are more details about it:
a. Create an image demo:devops on Application Server 3 from a container ubuntu_latest that is running on same server.

Solutions:- 
ğŸ› ï¸ Step-by-Step Instructions

Access Application Server 3 SSH into the server where the container is running:
ssh user@application-server-3

Verify the Running Container Confirm the container ubuntu_latest is active:
docker ps | grep ubuntu_latest

Commit the Container to an Image Use the docker commit command to create a new image from the container:
docker commit ubuntu_latest demo:devops

ubuntu_latest: Name or ID of the running container
demo:devops: Name and tag of the new image

Verify the New Image Check that the image was created successfully:
docker images | grep demo
